        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "A simpler (breaking) alternative: instead of storing `metadata[capture_id].range`, store `metadata[capture_id].offset` and then in `vim.treesitter.get_range()` we can apply this offset per node, regardless of whether it was collected in a quantified capture or not. Plugins reading `metadata[capture_id].range` will get borked I'd assume (unless we keep that metadata value around for bwc and just don't read it here?)",
